{"cursor":"11939","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox radio show |show_name = Music and the Spoken Word |image = Music and\nthe Spoken Word program logo.svg |imagesize = 250px |format = Worship, classical\n|runtime = 27 minutes, 56 seconds |country = United States of America |language\n= English |home_station = KSL NewsRadio (radio) KSL-TV (television)\n|starring = Mormon Tabernacle Choir Orchestra at Temple Square |announcer =\nLloyd D. Newell    ( - present) J. Spencer Kinard    ( - ) Alan Jensen    ( - ) Richard L. Evans    ( - ) Ted Kimball    ( - ) |creator = Earl J. Glade |writer = Joni Hilton Luke Howard Roger Miller Lloyd D. Newell Heidi S. Swinton\n|director = Lynn Clayson Wendy Crossman Michael Hunter Robert O.\nMorton Lee Wessman Nathan K. Wright |producer = Edward J. Payne Eldon Griffin |rec_location = Salt Lake Tabernacle and Conference Center Salt Lake City, Utah, United States |first_aired = (radio) since\n(television) |num_episodes = 4,374 (as of ) |audio_format = Stereophonic sound\n|opentheme = Gently Raise the Sacred Strain |othertheme = As the Dew from Heaven\nDistilling |endtheme = God Be with You Till We Meet Again |website =\nhttp://www.musicandthespokenword.com/ }}\n\n'Music and the Spoken Word' is a weekly 30-minute radio and television program\nof inspiring messages and music produced by Bonneville Communications with music\nperformed by the Mormon Tabernacle Choir (often accompanied by the Salt Lake\nTabernacle organ and the Orchestra at Temple Square).\n\nThe radio program is distributed by the CBS Radio Network and its broadcast\ncenter is KSL (AM) Radio, a Salt Lake City station owned by Bonneville\nInternational Corporation, which is in turn owned by The Church of Jesus Christ\nof Latter-day Saints (LDS Church). KSL is a former CBS Radio affiliate; it\nswitched to ABC Radio, now Citadel Media in 2005. In addition, it is currently\nbroadcast by over 2,000 television and radio stations\nworldwide. [http://www.musicandthespokenword.com/history/ksl.php Music and\nthe Spoken Word History: KSL], Bonneville Communications. Retrieved on March 28,\n2007. [http://www.musicandthespokenword.com/international.php Music\nand the Spoken Word History: International], Bonneville Communications.\nRetrieved on March 28, 2007.\n","linknr":213,"url":"Music_and_the_Spoken_Word","recorded":1375083796,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Music_and_the_Spoken_Word&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Music_and_the_Spoken_Word&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:Music_and_the_Spoken_Word_program_logo.svg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/a9/Music_and_the_Spoken_Word_program_logo.svg/250px-Music_and_the_Spoken_Word_program_logo.svg.png","/wiki/Worship_music","/wiki/Classical_music","/wiki/United_States","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/a4/Flag_of_the_United_States.svg/23px-Flag_of_the_United_States.svg.png","/wiki/United_States_of_America","/wiki/English_language","/wiki/KSL_(radio)","/wiki/KSL-TV","/wiki/Mormon_Tabernacle_Choir","/wiki/Orchestra_at_Temple_Square","/wiki/Lloyd_D._Newell","/wiki/J._Spencer_Kinard","/wiki/Richard_L._Evans","/wiki/Ted_Kimball","/wiki/Earl_J._Glade","/wiki/Lloyd_D._Newell","/wi